Change the project structure to contain subprojects. Add Data project to handle the data logic. Add Web project to handle the web server logic. It will consume the Data project.

Add main Database Models

- Add custom User class model inherited from IdentityUser - Scaffold again the Net Core Identity pages to use the custom user class. - Add many-to-many relationship between items and categories. - Add new migrations (V3 latest) to reflect the new database changes.

- Add custom User class model inherited from IdentityUser - Scaffold again the Net Core Identity pages to use the custom user class. - Add many-to-many relationship between items and categories. - Add new migrations (V3 latest) to reflect the new database changes.

- Add repository pattern to Data project. - Make a CRUD interface for repositories to be used for easier dependency injection. - Make a generic base repository that implements the CRUD interface. - Make separate repositories for each Entity that inherit the base repository (no code duplication purposes)
Give up the services pattern idea because it will be an overkill for this pretty small project. Might be added later.
